<font color="#FF0000">A SICK STORY!</font><br>
<tt>Fri Sep 19 11:43:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Okay, so nobody cares about Mustang being held POW by the Booger Monster... Well, I'm gonna tell you about it anyway!<br>
I low-crawled a hundred and ninety four miles to the local VA hospital... I lay at the entrance of the emergency room for five days... usually, it is only three days but I screwed up and wore my camouflaged pajamas... they didn't even see me until the second day.  A Pakistani and a Bangladeshi doctor got into a terrible argument over who was going to get my watch.  I tried to communicate with them in Plains Indian Sign language... the only message that they could interpret was the raised middle finger.<br>
Distraught, I low-crawled to my fee basis doctor... this time I wore an old Marine Corps dress uniform that I found in a dumpster...it worked... I had become highly visible.  The entire staff worked diligently to tend to my needs and get me off  the property... they kept mumbling something about &quot;...bright gaudy colors and lowering of real estate values.&quot;<br>
After signing the title of my farm over to the attending physician he informed me that I was very sick.  I asked for a second opinion...and he replied, &quot;you are very ugly too!&quot;  I traded my watch (which didn't work) for some antibiotics (which didn't work).  He advised my pretty wife to keep me out of bed for several weeks so that I could get some rest.<br>
Finally, I took matters into my own hands.  Clenching an old flight manual between my teeth, I removed both lungs with my P-38 (one at a time) and washed them in a mixture of concentrated Kool Aid and Thunderbird Wine... I sewed them back in place with a rusty fish hook and a piece of parachute chord.  It was rough the first couple of hours... the tremendous weight of my medals pressing down on my muscular chest caused my weakened lungs to work extra hard.  I recall lying there craving a Spam and artichoke sandwich.<br>
I managed to lecture the graduate students at Pittsburgh State last Wednesday... had a good time.  PTSD is in abeyance now because my thirteen year old is driving me crazy instead.  Wife is in good form after her weekly beating.  All is well on the reservation.  Glad to see that Chet appreciates good poetry.  Do you guys know anybody who has a large ostentatious watch for sale?<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
<p><code>-- plain and simple  (you know) </code><p>


